  "texts": [
    "This is illustrated in Figure 1.",
    "An I-graded local system V 0 is entirely determined up to isomorphism by the data of its irregular class Θ and the equivalence class C of its monodromy under graded automorphisms (acting by conjugation).",
    "We will refer to the pair (Θ, C) as the formal data of V 0.",
    "This language enables us to have a more geometric formulation of the Levelt-Turrittin decomposition:",
    "In turn, to any algebraic connection (E, ∇) on the affine line is associated (by considering the corresponding connection on the formal punctured disk at ∞) a formal local system V 0 → ∂ (which is I-graded)."
  ],
